 <!-- Introduction -->
 <purpose>
This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the representation of structured data holders for recording evaluated values of simple or compound criteria as well as slots to record the evaluation results of a condition being evaluated.

 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
   	<li>The identification of the condition evaluated</li>
	<li>The identification of the object evaluated</li>
	<li>The recording of parameter values evaluated and evaluation outcome</li>
	<li>The recording of the result of condition evaluated</li>

 </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
   	<li>Evaluation of objects not identifiable by an ISO 10303 specified entity and its associated identifier</li>	
   	<li>The computation or conversion of parameter values</li>
	<li>Parameter values directly from physical signals</li>
	<li>Identification and access of objects implied by a class hierarchy</li>

 </outscope>

